column2: Histologically or cytologically-documented, advanced solid tumor of one of the following types:
column4: Anal Squamous Cell Carcinoma, Biliary Adenocarcinoma, Neuroendocrine Tumors, Endometrial Carcinoma, Cervical Squamous Cell Carcinoma, Vulvar Squamous Cell Carcinoma, Small Cell Lung Carcinoma, Mesothelioma, Thyroid Carcinoma, Salivary Gland Carcinoma
(gallbladder or biliary tree (intrahepatic or extrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma) except Ampulla of Vater cancers)

column2: Any advanced solid tumor (including Colorectal Carcinoma [CRC]) which is Mismatch Repair Deficient (dMMR)/MSI-H in participants from mainland China who are of Chinese descent.
Any advanced solid tumor that has failed at least one line of therapy and is TMB-H (10 mut/Mb, F1CDx assay), excluding dMMR/MSI-H tumors.
column6: At least one line of standard of care systemic therapy
column7: TMB-H ≥ 10 mut/Mb & !dMMR/MSI-H & ☓ standard of care systemic therapy

column2: Diagnosis of immunodeficiency or receiving systemic steroid therapy or any other form of immunosuppressive therapy within 7 days prior to the first dose of study treatment
column6: Systemic steroid therapy or immunosuppressive therapy
column7: NOT (Immunodeficiency) AND NOT (receiving systemic steroid therapy or any other form of immunosuppressive therapy within 7 days prior to the first dose of study treatment)

column2: Active autoimmune disease that has required systemic treatment in the past 2 years
Prior anti-cancer monoclonal antibody (mAb) within 4 weeks prior to study Day 1 or not recovered from an adverse event caused by mAbs administered more than 4 weeks earlier
column7: Not recovered from an adverse event caused by mAbs administered more than 4 weeks earlier OR (monoclonal antibody therapy within 4 weeks prior to study Day 1)

column2: Prior chemotherapy, targeted small molecule therapy, or radiation therapy within 2 weeks of study Day 1 or not recovered from adverse events caused by a previously administered agent
column6: Chemotherapy, targeted small molecule therapy, radiation therapy
column7: Criterion Rule: (!(Chemotherapy OR Targeted Small Molecule Therapy OR Radiation Therapy) AND (Not Recovered From Adverse Events))

column2: Known additional malignancy within 2 years prior to enrollment with the exception of curatively treated basal cell carcinoma of the skin, squamous cell carcinoma of the skin and/or curatively resected in situ cancers
Has known glioblastoma multiforme of the brain stem
Has a history of (noninfectious) pneumonitis/interstitial lung disease that required steroids or has current pneumonitis/interstitial lung disease.
Known history of Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV)
Known active Hepatitis B or C
Known history of active tuberculosis (TB, Bacillus tuberculosis)
Has had an allogenic tissue/solid organ transplant
column7: Not eligible if have had an allogenic tissue/solid organ transplant
